A project proposal shall be reviewed for scientific merit as follows:
Adequacy of prior research and theory in providing a basis for the research;
Adequacy of methods;
Adequacy of environment, facilities, equipment, available equipment, and research atmosphere;
Qualifications and productivity of the PI and key staff;
Time commitments of the PI and key staff;
Availability of subjects or patients where relevant;
Adequacy of procedures for assessing the effect of interventions on recovery; and
Other factors that affect the potential of the applicants to successfully address the research objectives.

A project shall be reviewed by the board for adherence to research priorities relating to experimental, clinical, or population-based studies that may:
Prevent or delay the development of diabetic disease;
Predict the development of diabetic vascular, neuronal, or musculo-skeletal complications;
Define the response of diabetic vascular, neuronal, or musculo-skeletal complications to existing therapies;
Reverse diabetic vascular, neuronal, or musculo-skeletal complications; or
Cure diabetic disease.
